http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Man-held-for-attempt-to-murder-daughter/article13982701.ece

The Holehonnur police have arrested a person on the charge of attempting to murder his daughter.Shivamurthappa (45), a farmer from Chandanakere village, is the arrested. According to police, his eldest daughter Shalini was in love with a youth from the same village and their marriage was fixed on January 6. Shivamurthappa had initially opposed the marriage but gave his consent later owing to the pressure exerted by relatives of both the sides. It is said that Shivamurthappa had told his relatives that his daughter had brought disrepute to him over this issue.Upset with the decision taken by Shalini to marry the boy of her choice, Shivamurthappa conspired to kill her. On Saturday night, he entered the room where his three daughters were asleep. Misidentifying his second daughter Shaila as his eldest daughter, he hit her with an iron bar and came out of the room. On hearing the hue and cry of the injured girl and her sister, neighbours rushed to the house, but he pretended ignorance.Shivamurthappa had even taken the injured Shaila to a private hospital in Manipal for treatment. The police who got suspicious over the behaviour of Shivamurthappa interrogated him. He then confessed to the crime.The police have booked a case under section 307 (attempt to murder) of the Indian Penal Code against him. Shaila was still being treated at a private hospital in Manipal.